  "updated_summary": "The Young Man with Curly Hair, holding a camera with a blue light, films himself on a moving bus, initially looking at his phone before smiling at the camera and sitting next to the Woman in Harvard Sweater, who is eating pizza. He gestures animatedly while discussing Harvard students and philosophizing about life being \"fake\" and \"pixels on screen,\" prompting laughter from the Woman in Harvard Sweater. The bus travels through an urban landscape with brick buildings. The scene shifts to the Young Man and the Woman, identified as Helen, walking on a lively campus path under overcast skies, with bare trees. The Young Man asks Helen if she's \"good,\" attributing her state to Harvard and mentioning they just left an \"entrepreneurship class.\" He inquires about her major, and she replies \"Neuroscience.\" They pass a Red-Brick Dormitory Building and a building with a Statue of Historical Figure. A YouTube screen recording shows college decision reaction videos, including one for Harvard. Returning to the campus walk, the Young Man questions Helen about her early admission to Harvard at 16. Helen explains graduating high school in three years and strong extracurriculars were key. The Woman in Harvard Sweater checks her phone and laughs as they continue their conversation. Later, the Young Man with Curly Hair, wearing a blue puffer jacket, walks briskly through the campus, passing the Red-Brick Dormitory Building, and asks the camera, \"Did you feel like your peers were like smarter than you?\" The Woman in Harvard Sweater walks beside him, smiling and glancing at her phone. The scene transitions to an indoor lecture hall where the Young Man is among the Lecture Hall Audience, reacting to a presentation and noting, \"next up we went to our second class, which was philosophy.\" The camera shows the Man in Blue Shirt, holding a red water bottle and yellow notepad, explaining \"utilitarianism\" and \"horrible things in the name of the greater good.\" The Young Man turns to his peers, including the Bearded Male Companion, sharing a laugh, with on-screen text reading 'Damn bro these are smart mof*s'. He invites the Bearded Male Companion into the video; he agrees and states his major is \"biomedical engineering,\" later confirming he is \"transferring to Harvard.\" The group exits the lecture hall and walks back outside into the campus environment. The Young Man adjusts his hair and continues engaging with his friends, including the Woman in Harvard Sweater, who is laughing and smiling. He concludes, \"My IQ's actually leveling up,\" maintaining his vlog-style narrative."
